[The HFMD outbreaks continue to spread through China with up to 12
000 children affected and 26 fatalities reported. The province of
Anhui has been hardest hit with almost 6000 cases, almost all of
which have been reported from the vicinity of Fuyang city where 22 of
the 26 deaths have occurred. In most provinces enterovirus 71 has
been confirmed as the cause of the infection.

In striking contrast in Taiwan 2 deaths have been reported among 60
serious cases, but the number of non-serious cases is not stated.
Here also enterovirus 71 has been confirmed as the cause of the outbreak.

A map of the provinces of China is available at
<http://www.chinamapxl.com/political-map.html>,
and a map of Anhui province showing the location of the city of
Fuyang in the northwest of the province is available at
<http://www.mapsofworld.com/china/provinces/anhui/map-of-anhui.html>.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of China and Taiwan can be
accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=36.5,103.9,4>. - Mod.CP]

[In the 2nd newswire, there is mention that HFMD has just recently
been added to the list of diseases to be reported to the central
level. As a result, there is an expected major increase in reported
numbers of cases as more provinces e change in regulations. What is
needed here to help monitor the actual progress of the outbreak will
be epidemic curves showing numbers of cases by date of onset, rather
than by date of report. - Mod.MPP]
